article.headline: S. Dakota 104, Midland Lutheran 71
article.story: VERMILLION, S.D. -- Jake Thomas made a school-record nine 3-pointers and scored a season-high 31 points in South Dakota's 104-71 win over Midland Lutheran on Sunday. Thomas, a freshman from Racine, Wis., was 9 of 12 from 3-point range and 11 of 14 overall. Louie Krogman added 18 points, and Mitchell Bouie had 15 for the Coyotes (4-3). Jason Ahrens led the Warriors (2-8) with 21 points.
